{
  "stem": "2581.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But the rest of us at home, we felt that our shield of protection-- our father-- was offended, was hurt.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They took this away from us, and I can't begin to describe that feeling of not so much for our father, that we felt our family is collapsing.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My father that we always considered the stronger and the protector, and all of a sudden, he was taken in by these people and beaten up to that way-- that way.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the conditions in town kept constantly deteriorating.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "More and more people were sent away to work.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "More people that were fine, comfortable, intelligent people were being destroyed, in spiritually and physically.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and one day, on the Purim day-- it was Purim-- they knew exactly how to hurt us, because everything that happened was in a Jew-- most of the worst things that used to happen were on a Jewish holiday.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was Purim.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And these-- went to-- the Gendarmes went to the-- to our rabbi and said, today, today is the holiday that the Jews celebrate for hanging Haman.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Haman.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He said, we want to show you that we are more humane than the Jews are.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "On this holiday, we  are not going to hang 10 people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We   will only hang two.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we want you to give us the two people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- and the-- and they said, we will come back tomorrow, and I want you to name us two people that we should hang them.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He said-- rabbi said, you don't have to come back tomorrow.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I'll give you right now.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Take me and my wife.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they hit him very-- you know, they beat them up very badly.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "How dare   he talk to them like that?",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
